    "\"source\": \\[\n",
    "\n",
    "\"\\# Note\\\\n\",\n",
    "\n",
    "\" \\* Here Regression follow an assumption that data to normal\n",
    "distribution like, here we need to remove skewness \\\\n\",\n",
    "\n",
    "\" through skewness transformation = LOG\n",
    "Transformation/sqrt/cuberoot\\\\n\",\n",
    "\n",
    "\" then check power transformer below with does log transformation as no\n",
    "negative values are present \"\n",
    "\n",
    "\\]\n",
    "\n",
    "},\n",
    "\n",
    "{\n",
    "\n",
    "\"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",

    "\"metadata\": {},\n",
    "\n",
    "\"outputs\": \\[\\],\n",
    "\n",
    "\"source\": \\[\n",
    "\n",
    "\"power = PowerTransformer()\\\\n\",\n",
    "\n",
    "\"for i in new_df.columns:\\\\n\",\n",
    "\n",
    "\" if np.abs(new_df\\[i\\].skew()) \\> 0.5: \\# as we know that the skew\n",
    "value is between -0.5 and 0.5 indicates that good distribution \\\\n\",\n",
    "\n",
    "\" new_df\\[\\[i\\]\\] = power.fit_transform(new_df\\[\\[i\\]\\])\"\n",
    "\n",
    "\\]\n",
    "\n",
    "},\n",
